channel.title: Wedding music
channel.description: Okay, we are trying to make our list of songs for our DJ, and we still don't have a song. It's driving me crazy. The wedding isn't until August 09, but i need to figure this stuff out now. Does anyone have any good suggestions for wedding reception music?

item.title: Wedding music
item.dc:creator: @T41 t4
item.description:
@T41 wrote:

Hmm, this is a bit tough for me due to the fact I mostly listen to Hard Rock/Metal. Here’s what I can think of:

311 - Love Song : http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mZqEqypU4cs
Green Day - Welcome to paradise : http://www.dailymotion.com/video/x24cqc_green-day-welcome-to-paradise_music
Marcy Playground - Sex and Candy : http://vids.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=vids.individual&videoid=2270355
Silversun Pickups - Panic Switch : http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZwIy6CJT7Ok
U2 - Mysterious Ways : http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_ZLjE_wuRE0

Chillest songs I can think of.

[quote=“Tico135, post:53, topic:236463”][quote author=srt8 link=topic=312057.msg2646446#msg2646446 date=1233263720]
eh, Travis helps when I ask him to but I guess it is mostly a girl thing. Like I have been registering us for presents and I’ve been trying to ask what he wants, but he doesn’t know.
[/quote]

Typical male. :P[/quote]

ehhh its true.

[quote=“srt8, post:57, topic:236463”][quote author=Tree link=topic=312057.msg2647304#msg2647304 date=1233319946]
@srt8 (off-topic): Out of curiosity, how did you meet Mopar? What are your opinions on this community and it’s userbase?
[/quote]

Travis’ best friend and my best friend at the time were dating and they decided to set us up on a blind date. On our first date he tried to explain to me what he did on here but I totally didn’t understand since I’m not computer literate at all.

I think it was like 3-5 months into dating before he actually showed me the sight. And oh goodness, I was very shocked with some of the conversations! lol[/quote]

wierd way to find out about mopar but oh well

personally I think you shouldn’t leave it up to mopar to decide. It should be the songs that you and your husband both love. Not what others would see you as or do if you played a certain song. Its your wedding, not theirs. don’t let them influence what you want for a wedding
